Joseph Olaoluwa lasaco Assurance Plc has approved the appointment of Dr Maria Phillips as its new chairman. This is coming after the Board of Directorsâ€™ meeting that held on October 7, according to a regulatory filing by the firm at the Nigerian Stock Exchange. Phillips is a successful chartered accountant who holds an ACCA from England and Wales; she speaks Yoruba, English and French fluently, according to the statement. It added that she was a director at Keystone Bank; a director, Lagos State Lottery Board; commissioner for Special Duties & Inter-Governmental Relations in Lagos State. She was also a Managing Director of Alma Beach Estate Ltd (a subsidiary of Rims Merchant Bank Limited) and a Managing Director, Maridot Ventures Limited. The statement said Philips was a renowned management / financial consultant to many companies and was at a time, the Divisional Commercial Manager of Property Division of the United African Company of Nigeria Plc. Copyright PUNCH.
